  "page-445": "<ul><li>palidecer, (pres. palidezco), to become pale.</li><li>pálido, -a, pale; ponerse ——, to turn pale.</li><li>palma, f., palm; —— de coco, coconut palm.</li><li>palmada, f., clapping of hands; dar ——s, to clap one's hands.</li><li>palo, m., stick, pole, log; —— de rosa, rosewood.</li><li>pampa, f., an extensive plain, pampas (of South America).</li><li>panadería, f., bakery.</li><li>panadero, m., baker.</li><li>panal, m., honeycomb.</li><li>Panamá, f., Panama.</li><li>Paolo, Ital., Paul.</li><li>papagayo, m., parrot.</li><li>papanatas, m., simpleton, fool.</li><li>papel, m., paper.</li><li>par, adj., similar, like.</li><li class=\" stretch-last-line\">par, m., pair, couple; a ——es, in pairs; de —— en</li></ul>",
